CSF 2.0 Core data (data/csf-core.json)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0 and its Core (Functions, Categories,
and Subcategory outcome statements) are works of the U.S. Government and are in
the public domain. The data file shipped here was generated from the official
machine-readable export of the NIST Cybersecurity and Privacy Reference Tool
(CPRT): https://csrc.nist.gov/projects/cprt

The generation is reproducible from the official source with:
    npm run build-csf-core
See scripts/build-csf-core.js for the exact extraction (it keeps the 22 CSF 2.0
Categories and drops withdrawn CSF v1.1 entries and "[Withdrawn]" placeholders,
yielding the 106 live Subcategory outcomes).

